\text{Suppose two different pairs of numbers have the same sum.}\\ \text{If they have the same sum, they also have the same product.}\\ \text{But if two pairs of numbers have both the same sum and product, the pairs are actually identical.}\\ \text{Since two things cannot be both different and the same, contradiction.}\\ 
